\chapter*{Disclaimers}

I wish that studies such as this weren’t necessary.
 They wouldn't be if we stopped considering pollination and many other natural processes as a “service” that non-human beings are offering to humans for our system’s functioning.
 They wouldn't be if we go back to recognizing how our habitat’s health determines our own health. 

We keep perceiving ourselves as damaging to the environment and not part of it, we want to "protect" nature while all other life forms are objectified and enslaved to our system. Every moral limit is gone. 

We need to recognize that we don’t save or protect flora or fauna. Our way of existing, our production and our relationships have to take into account a collective and mutual care.

Some populations do exist as part of the ecosystem they live in, participating to natural processes.

Once we will recognize or just remember the interdependence of human and non-human life, without referring everything to profit it would be easier to build a different relationship with the environment and show solidarity with it \parencite{barcaForzeDiRiproduzione2024}.


